Flapmax and Microsoft have announced the end of their FAST Acceleration Programme for 12 Startups. According to the firm, it held a transition event to commemorate the end of the 12-week programme and create an avenue for the Startups to be introduced to opportunities for business growth and market visibility. They added that the startups were chosen from 800+ startups applications received across Africa to participate in the cohort. In a statement, they said, “It is worthy of note that Microsoft is partnering with strategic partners across Africa and beyond to support the enablement of over 10,000 Small and Medium Scale Enterprises and Startups to grow and develop their businesses for economy growth and creation of opportunities for young people.” The Chief Executive Officer of Flapmax, Dave Ojika, said the startups’ partnership with it and Microsoft will continue to provide the startups with the needed support for growth.